  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dd4 \u0db8\u0dcf\u0dc3 5\u0d9a \u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dda \u0d85\u0db4\u0db1\u0dba\u0db1 \u0da9\u0ddc.\u0db6\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1 5\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Exports of $ 5 billion in the last 5 months",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Earnings from commodity exports in May 2022 increased by 9.9% to US $ 980.2 million compared to the previous year, according to the Export Development Board of Sri Lanka.",
        "This was mainly due to higher export earnings from garments and textiles, coconut products and electrical and electronic components.",
        "Accordingly, Sri Lanka's export earnings for the past five months as a whole have reached US $ 5 billion, according to the Export Development Board.",
        "In addition, service exports for the January-May 2022 period were estimated at $ 1,472.7 million, an increase of 93.3% over the corresponding period of 2021.",
        "The services estimated by the Export Development Board consist of Export ICT / BPM, Construction, Financial Services and Transport and Logistics."
      ],
